<i>or maybe both of them,</i>

01:35:41.640 --> 01:35:45.964
<i>two outsiders, took everybody
on Wall Street for a ride?</i>

01:35:46.080 --> 01:35:47.496
<i>Yeah, it really looks
like they did.</i>

01:35:47.520 --> 01:35:49.761
- Yeah.
- And Acosta has vanished?

01:35:49.880 --> 01:35:52.486
With hundreds of millions
of dollars.

01:35:52.640 --> 01:35:56.008
Kenny Wells has always
maintained his innocence,

01:35:56.120 --> 01:35:58.771
<i>that he was duped
along with everyone else.</i>

01:35:58.880 --> 01:36:01.611
<i>Given that,
what do you make of this?</i>

01:36:03.080 --> 01:36:07.847
Kenny Wells,
a fool or a mastermind?

01:36:09.720 --> 01:36:12.087
<i>It's</i> a <i>very good
question, Roger.</i>

01:36:32.360 --> 01:36:33.771
Um...

01:36:36.120 --> 01:36:40.409
Mike-Mike Acosta was my friend
and, uh, my partner.

01:36:40.560 --> 01:36:41.891
Um...

01:36:43.160 --> 01:36:46.004
and he-he betrayed me.

01:36:46.120 --> 01:36:49.681
I-I know as CEO
of Washoe Mining

01:36:49.800 --> 01:36:51.928
it's my responsibility to know

01:36:52.040 --> 01:36:54.930
everything that's going on,
and I... I didn't.

01:36:56.200 --> 01:36:58.407
It's not an excuse.

01:36:58.520 --> 01:37:00.409
All right?
I sincerely apologize

01:37:00.520 --> 01:37:04.161
to everybody and anybody
that lost on their investments.

01:37:07.360 --> 01:37:09.931
Come on, Mike.

01:37:10.040 --> 01:37:12.042
Mikey, come on in, man.

01:37:12.160 --> 01:37:14.891
All right?

01:37:15.000 --> 01:37:16.650
What happened, huh?

01:37:33.920 --> 01:37:36.127
- Howard.
- I saw you on TV.

01:37:36.240 --> 01:37:39.164
- Hey, man, can I talk to you
for a minute, please? -No.

01:37:39.280 --> 01:37:41.169
Look, I just want to know
where my money went.

01:37:41.280 --> 01:37:43.336
- Come on! -Don't know anything
about it, okay? -Mr. Wells,

01:37:43.360 --> 01:37:46.204
Mr. Wells, exactly when
will you be departing?

01:37:46.320 --> 01:37:49.164
Uh, later. A few days or so.
I'll let you know.

01:37:49.280 --> 01:37:52.045
- We just need to talk about
your bill, sir. <i>-I'll</i> be down.

01:37:52.160 --> 01:37:53.525
We'll settle it up.

01:38:58.760 --> 01:39:00.842
Do I need a lawyer?

01:39:00.960 --> 01:39:03.406
Do you need a lawyer?

01:39:06.760 --> 01:39:08.683
Right answer.

01:39:20.720 --> 01:39:22.688
<i>How'd you meet Michael Acosta?</i>

01:39:26.000 --> 01:39:29.243
The, uh, first time
or the second time?

01:39:29.400 --> 01:39:31.767
How'd you meet him, Wells?

01:39:33.720 --> 01:39:36.644
It was April... of '88.

01:39:38.520 --> 01:39:40.727
Yeah, I was
on the balls of my ass.

01:39:40.840 --> 01:39:43.525
Scrambling.

01:39:43.640 --> 01:39:46.803
Not exactly uncharted waters
for me, but...

01:39:46.920 --> 01:39:49.287
I was in deep.

01:39:57.360 --> 01:39:59.010
I think it's pretty unlikely

01:39:59.120 --> 01:40:01.122
we'll ever see
your partner again.

01:40:03.680 --> 01:40:06.160
- What are you talking about?
- A lot of very powerful people

01:40:06.280 --> 01:40:08.203
are very angry
at Michael Acosta.

01:40:12.200 --> 01:40:13.690
Well, what happened?

01:40:13.800 --> 01:40:14.881
What happened?

01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:17.685
$17 billion of value
disappeared overnight.

01:40:17.800 --> 01:40:19.086
Mike Acosta
waves good-bye to you

01:40:19.240 --> 01:40:21.322
in the ballroom downstairs
and goes back to Indonesia

01:40:21.440 --> 01:40:23.841
<i>on a jet chartered
with Washoe funds.</i>

01:40:23.960 --> 01:40:26.725
<i>And then he does
a disappearing act.</i>

01:40:26.840 --> 01:40:28.888
<i>But this you know.</i>

01:40:29.040 --> 01:40:32.408
<i>First, he's locked out
of the assay lab in Kalimantan</i>

01:40:32.520 --> 01:40:34.921
<i>by the minister of the interior.</i>

01:40:35.040 --> 01:40:36.849
<i>- So he goes back to Jakarta...</i>
- Mr. <i>Acosta,</i>

01:40:36.960 --> 01:40:38.371
please walk with with me.

01:40:38.480 --> 01:40:40.369
<i>Where he's immediately detained</i>

01:40:40.480 --> 01:40:42.448
<i>by the Indonesian military.</i>

01:40:44.080 --> 01:40:45.445
<i>And they hold him</i>

01:40:45.600 --> 01:40:47.682
<i>while they try to reproduce
for themselves</i>

01:40:47.800 --> 01:40:50.121
<i>the lab results claimed
by Washoe.</i>

01:40:51.760 --> 01:40:54.604
Which, of course,
they are unable to do.

01:40:54.720 --> 01:40:57.371
Now, at this point,

01:40:57.480 --> 01:41:00.484
either he's being transferred
to an actual prison, or...

01:41:00.600 --> 01:41:02.409
he's bribed one of the officers.

01:41:02.520 --> 01:41:03.567
Either way,

01:41:03.680 --> 01:41:05.284
<i>he's on a military helicopter.</i>

01:41:07.080 --> 01:41:10.163
<i>They fly north, loosely
tracking the Kensana River.</i>

01:41:57.680 --> 01:42:01.810
<i>A thousand feet up,
over the Kensana...</i>

01:42:01.920 --> 01:42:04.491
<i>Mike Acosta takes a header.</i>

01:42:15.040 --> 01:42:17.805
No way.

01:42:17.920 --> 01:42:20.605
No fucking way.

01:42:20.720 --> 01:42:22.529
He either faked it,

01:42:22.640 --> 01:42:24.802
or he paid to have
this-this bullshit story

01:42:24.920 --> 01:42:26.445
you're telling put out.

01:42:26.560 --> 01:42:30.804
$164 million goes a long way
in Indonesia.

01:42:30.920 --> 01:42:33.446
They found a body.

01:42:48.840 --> 01:42:51.241
<i>Hands and face were eaten away,</i>

01:42:51.360 --> 01:42:54.284
<i>probably by wild pigs.</i>

01:42:54.400 --> 01:42:56.971
Sure this is him?

01:42:57.080 --> 01:42:59.401
I'm not sure of anything...

01:42:59.520 --> 01:43:04.208
<i>except Mike Acosta traded
water filters for river gold.</i>

01:43:04.360 --> 01:43:05.930
<i>But now
the Indonesian government</i>

01:43:06.040 --> 01:43:07.326
<i>have gone unusually quiet</i>

01:43:07.440 --> 01:43:09.090
on the subject.

01:43:09.240 --> 01:43:10.844
There was an autopsy

01:43:10.960 --> 01:43:12.962
corroborating the identity
of the body.

01:43:14.280 --> 01:43:16.851
<i>They then sealed the report...</i>

01:43:18.560 --> 01:43:20.608
cremated the remains.

01:43:20.720 --> 01:43:25.169
Interestingly,
Danny Suharto, your friend...

01:43:25.280 --> 01:43:28.170
dumped a lot of stock as well.

01:43:28.280 --> 01:43:31.124
So the Suhartos
are even richer now.

01:43:31.240 --> 01:43:34.562
Mike Acosta is ostensibly
dead and buried, and...

01:43:34.680 --> 01:43:37.001
$164 million is still missing.

01:43:37.120 --> 01:43:40.488
And the only question...

01:43:40.600 --> 01:43:42.807
I'm left with is...

01:43:42.920 --> 01:43:45.446
whether or not
you were in on it.

01:43:47.560 --> 01:43:49.801
I...

01:43:49.920 --> 01:43:53.242
- I can't believe it.
- Can't believe what?

01:43:53.360 --> 01:43:56.921
No, look, th-this business...

01:43:57.080 --> 01:43:59.651
had written Mike off
years ago, all right?

01:43:59.760 --> 01:44:01.171
They called his theories crap.

01:44:01.280 --> 01:44:03.203
But...

01:44:03.320 --> 01:44:05.163
there's no way.

01:44:05.280 --> 01:44:07.203
He wouldn't, he fucking couldn't

01:44:07.320 --> 01:44:09.448
let this be
the last word on him.

01:44:09.560 --> 01:44:13.167
- No fucking way. -You talking
about Acosta or yourself?

01:44:23.000 --> 01:44:26.527
All right, look. We-we-we were
running out of money, right?

01:44:26.640 --> 01:44:29.166
And I was practically dying
from malaria.

01:44:29.320 --> 01:44:31.971
I gave Mike
the last dollar to my name.

01:44:32.080 --> 01:44:34.765
And I made him promise me
something, I said, "Mike...

01:44:34.880 --> 01:44:38.327
don't let me die out here
for nothing."

01:44:43.320 --> 01:44:46.324
A few weeks later,
I came to, and...

01:44:46.440 --> 01:44:48.408
Mike was there.

01:44:52.000 --> 01:44:54.082
He said, "We got...

01:44:54.200 --> 01:44:56.362
"we got a strike, Kenny.

01:44:57.640 --> 01:45:00.007
We got a goddamn gold mine."

01:45:04.520 --> 01:45:09.447
And th-there's no way that
he set out to swindle anyone.

01:45:09.560 --> 01:45:12.211
He just needed
to buy a little more time.

01:45:17.320 --> 01:45:19.368
And he didn't want
to let me down.

01:45:19.480 --> 01:45:23.326
- You're fuckin' lyin'.
- Levine, sit down!

01:45:23.440 --> 01:45:25.204
You want to talk
about the truth?

01:45:25.320 --> 01:45:26.890
All right,
let's talk about the truth.

01:45:27.000 --> 01:45:29.162
The only truth here is,
when everybody's getting rich,

01:45:29.280 --> 01:45:32.090
nobody gives a shit
about the truth.

01:45:32.200 --> 01:45:35.283
Come the fuck on.
All anyone had to do was look,

01:45:35.400 --> 01:45:37.129
open their eyes.

01:45:37.240 --> 01:45:40.323
Man, the-the gold was wrong,
the find was too good.

01:45:40.440 --> 01:45:43.011
There were red flags everywhere.

01:45:43.120 --> 01:45:44.770
Why did no one look?

01:45:44.880 --> 01:45:46.848
'Cause no one wanted
to fucking know.

01:45:46.960 --> 01:45:48.849
We all wanted to believe.

01:45:48.960 --> 01:45:50.883
Me, you,
fucking everybody. Why?

01:45:52.360 --> 01:45:55.648
Because we were all making
so much fucking money, man.

01:45:55.760 --> 01:45:58.001
That's the truth.

01:45:58.160 --> 01:46:00.845
That's been going on
for fucking centuries!

01:46:02.520 --> 01:46:05.683
Oh, fuck...

01:46:08.720 --> 01:46:11.291
Were you aware Mike Acosta
was salting

01:46:11.400 --> 01:46:13.801
- the Washoe core samples?
- No.

01:46:13.920 --> 01:46:15.365
You had no knowledge

01:46:15.480 --> 01:46:18.324
<i>Mike Acosta
was perpetrating a fraud?</i>

01:46:18.440 --> 01:46:20.807
<i>- No.
- You were not in collusion</i>

01:46:20.920 --> 01:46:23.810
<i>with Mike Acosta
on the Kensana gold strike?</i>

01:46:23.920 --> 01:46:27.845
No, man, I fucking thought
I won the lottery.

01:46:27.960 --> 01:46:31.362
Did you profit
from the Kensana fraud?

01:46:33.680 --> 01:46:36.126
- No. -Did anyone
close to you profit?

01:46:37.840 --> 01:46:40.411
My friends lost money.

01:46:40.520 --> 01:46:42.409
My neighbors lost money.

01:46:42.520 --> 01:46:44.568
Me...

01:46:44.680 --> 01:46:47.251
I lost everything.

01:46:50.120 --> 01:46:52.600
You know
what the truth of it is?

01:46:54.040 --> 01:46:56.202
I never really cared
about money.

01:46:57.280 --> 01:46:59.806
I cared about gold.

01:46:59.920 --> 01:47:02.127
And it's different, Jennings.

01:47:02.240 --> 01:47:04.288
It's fucking different.

01:47:23.320 --> 01:47:26.688
Interview terminated
with Kenny Wells...

01:47:26.800 --> 01:47:29.724
6:45 a.m.,

01:47:29.880 --> 01:47:33.407
October 17, 1988.

01:47:33.520 --> 01:47:34.806
Interview conducted by myself,

01:47:34.920 --> 01:47:37.127
Paul K. Jennings,
special agent.

01:47:37.240 --> 01:47:40.403
Also present,
agents Levine and Banks,

01:47:40.520 --> 01:47:42.409
Federal Bureau of Investigation,

01:47:42.520 --> 01:47:44.329
district of Nevada, Reno.

01:47:56.600 --> 01:47:58.728
Mr. Kenny Wells...

01:48:01.640 --> 01:48:03.927
you are free to go.

01:48:05.600 --> 01:48:08.490
Well, lookee there.

01:48:08.600 --> 01:48:10.841
Somebody believes me.

01:48:12.640 --> 01:48:14.961
I wouldn't go overboard.

01:48:15.080 --> 01:48:18.562
In fact,
I wouldn't leave the state,

01:48:18.720 --> 01:48:21.326
or start buying new stuff
or chartering

01:48:21.440 --> 01:48:23.016
- any more jets.
- I gotta sneak by the guy

01:48:23.040 --> 01:48:24.896
at the front desk 'cause
I can't pay the hotel bill.

01:48:24.920 --> 01:48:27.810
I can't be a party
to that information.

01:48:28.880 --> 01:48:31.167
Good luck, Mr. Wells.

01:48:31.280 --> 01:48:34.250
We'll be keeping an eye on you.

01:48:39.760 --> 01:48:42.081
What are you gonna do now,
Wells?

01:50:03.320 --> 01:50:04.845
Hey, Kenny.

01:50:04.960 --> 01:50:06.480
I-I'm still worried
about that mulberry

01:50:06.560 --> 01:50:08.961
- over the back fence.
- Yeah. I know, Hart.

01:50:09.120 --> 01:50:10.804
It's good to see you.

01:50:10.920 --> 01:50:12.809
Good to see you, too, Kenny.

01:50:43.480 --> 01:50:45.562
Can I come in?

01:51:21.520 --> 01:51:24.046
- You want coffee?
- Yeah, sure.

01:51:29.920 --> 01:51:32.207
This place looks great.

01:51:35.800 --> 01:51:38.007
So do you, Kay.

01:51:42.680 --> 01:51:44.330
I made curtains.

01:51:44.440 --> 01:51:47.046
From that fabric.

01:51:47.160 --> 01:51:48.491
Hmm.

01:51:51.720 --> 01:51:54.326
Some stuff came for you,
some mail.

01:52:43.400 --> 01:52:44.811
What?

01:52:44.920 --> 01:52:47.526
What is it?

